<exercise id="fs-idm18229840">
<problem id="fs-idm18229584">
<para id="fs-idm263612624">Why is the formation of slag useful during the smelting of iron?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm37965216">
<para id="fs-idm37964960">The CaSiO<sub>3</sub> slag is less dense than the molten iron, so it can easily be separated. Also, the floating slag layer creates a barrier that prevents the molten iron from exposure to O<sub>2</sub>, which would oxidize the Fe back to Fe<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub>.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
