<exercise id="fs-idm278997936">
<problem id="fs-idm278997680">
<para id="fs-idm278997424">Predict the products of the following reactions and balance the equations.</para>
<para id="fs-idm115177312">(a) Zn is added to a solution of Cr<sub>2</sub>(SO<sub>4</sub>)<sub>3</sub> in acid.</para>
<para id="fs-idm217652304">(b) FeCl<sub>2</sub> is added to a solution containing an excess of <m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mrow><m:mtext>Cr</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:msub><m:mtext>O</m:mtext><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:msub><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mn>2−</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> in hydrochloric acid.</para>
<para id="fs-idm207844576">(c) Cr<sup>2+</sup> is added to <m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mrow><m:mtext>Cr</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:msub><m:mtext>O</m:mtext><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:msub><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mn>2−</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> in acid solution.</para>
<para id="fs-idm265782768">(d) Mn is heated with CrO<sub>3</sub>.</para>
<para id="fs-idm229278448">(e) CrO is added to 2HNO<sub>3</sub> in water.</para>
<para id="fs-idm229277680">(f) FeCl<sub>3</sub> is added to an aqueous solution of NaOH.</para>
</problem>
